                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12134c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-16T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 16, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Department’s 90, June 15, 4 p.m. and your 192, June 15, 4 p.m. and 193, June
                    15, 6 p.m. The Department accepts your judgment that it would be undesirable to
                    refer to the possibility of termination <pb facs="0866" n="858" xml:id="pg_858"
                    /> of aid under the Lend-Lease Act and the instructions contained in the
                    Department’s 90 are modified accordingly. Please use your best endeavors to
                    dissuade the Turkish Government from signing the proposed pact, using the
                    arguments outlined in the second sentence of the Department’s 90 and in
                    paragraph 2 of your 193.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
